  "text": "Fat was the villain for thirty years. I bought low-fat everything. They added sugar to make up for it. We got worse. Turns out the type of fat matters. Avocado, half on toast keeps you full till noon. Olive oil, not a drizzle, an actual pour. Walnuts, one handful, done. Salmon, twice a week. That's the whole strategy. Nothing here is complicated. It's just fat that doesn't work against you. Recipes at www.dailylifehacks.com. Free, every week, no drama.",
